<TITLE> Demo at 2 RMG factories </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, May 24 (bdnews24.com)  Workers of two garment factories at Ashulia observed work-stoppage on different demands on Monday. Hearing of the agitation, police took position in front of the two factories. Sirajul Islam, officer in charge of Ashulia Police Station, confirmed to bdnews24.com about the unrest. He said additional police were deployed and kept on alert to avoid untoward circumstances. Police said workers of A M Design Limited, situated at Jamgora, started demonstrating Monday noon demanding removal of general manager (production) Mohammad Sujon and director Motahar Uddin. Workers say that the two officials were abusive towards the workers. There were even allegations of harassing female workers in their offices. The workers threatened strict movement if the two officials were not removed. In another incident, workers of Setara Group of the same area went on work stoppage from Monday morning pressing for 12-point demands. The demands include stopping workers' repression and summary dismissals, increasing attendance bonus and paying the current month's wages. Workers said that the strike would continue until their demands were met. bdnews2
